{"meta": {"centerNodeId": "taxonomy-species-melithreptus-validirostris", "centerNodeType": "taxonomy", "generatedAt": "2026-05-28T16:28:22", "includedNodeCount": 3, "includedLinkCount": 2, "layoutMode": "precomputed-static"}, "center": {"id": "taxonomy-species-melithreptus-validirostris", "name": "Strong-billed honeyeater", "type": "taxonomy"}, "nodes": [{"id": "taxonomy-species-melithreptus-validirostris", "name": "Strong-billed honeyeater", "latinName": "Melithreptus validirostris", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "species", "summary": "Strong-billed honeyeater（Melithreptus validirostris）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联1种鸟类，如Strong-billed honeyeater。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 1, "x": -246.97, "y": 393.97, "z": -638.34}, {"id": "bird-strong-billed-honeyeater-c69ed5c6", "name": "Strong-billed honeyeater", "englishName": "Strong-billed honeyeater", "latinName": "Melithreptus validirostris", "type": "bird", "status": "VU", "summary": "The strong-billed honeyeater (Melithreptus validirostris) is a species of bird in the family Meliphagidae. It is one of two species of the genus Melithreptus endemic to Tasmania. Its natural habitat is temperate forest. Taxonomy The strong-billed honeyeater was first described by ornithologist John Gould in 1837. Its specific name is derived from the Latin words validus 'strong', and rostrum 'bill'. It is a member of the genus Melithreptus, with several species of similar size and (apart from the brown-headed honeyeater) black-headed appearance, in the honeyeater family, Meliphagidae. Molecular markers show that the strong-billed honeyeater separated from the common ancestor of the brown-headed and black-chinned honeyeaters between 6.7 and 3.4 million years ago. The next closest relative outside the genus is the much larger, but similarly marked, blue-faced honeyeater. More recently, DNA analysis has shown honeyeaters to be related to the Pardalotidae (pardalotes), Acanthizidae (Australian warblers, scrubwrens, thornbills, etc.), and the Maluridae (Australian fairy-wrens) in the large superfamily Meliphagoidea. Description A mid-sized honeyeater at 16.5–17.5 cm (6.5–7 in) in length, it is olive-brown above and pale grey-brown below, with a black head, nape and throat, a pale blue to off-white patch over the eye, and a white crescent on the nape. Juveniles have brownish crowns, lemon-tinged nape, and an orange base of bill. Its call is a loud cheep cheep, or a churring. Ecology The strong-billed honeyeater is found in mature forest with large trees, such as Eucalyptus regnans and E. delegatensis. Its diet is principally insects and various other invertebrates, which it hunts on tree trunks, supplemented by nectar and fallen fruit. Although both species are widespread in Tasmania, the Strong-billed rarely overlaps in site and foraging with the black-headed honeyeater. Breeding Strong-billed honeyeaters may nest from September to January, breeding once or twice during this time. The nest is a thick-walled bowl of grasses and bits of bark in the fork of a tall tree, usually a eucalypt. Two or three eggs are laid, 22 x 17 mm in size, and shiny, buff-pink, sparsely spotted with red-brown. References External links Image at ADW", "shortSummary": "The strong-billed honeyeater (Melithreptus validirostris) is a species of bird in the family Meliphagidae. It is one of two species of the…", "habitats": ["温带森林", "成熟森林"], "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/bd/Melithreptus_validirostris_-_Myrtle_forest.jpg/960px-Melithreptus_validirostris_-_Myrtle_forest.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-melithreptus", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-melithreptus-validirostris", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-melithreptus", "species": "taxonomy-species-melithreptus-validirostris"}, "expandable": true, "x": -246.97, "y": 393.97, "z": -630.63}, {"id": "taxonomy-genus-melithreptus", "name": "Melithreptus", "latinName": "Melithreptus", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "genus", "summary": "Melithreptus（Melithreptus）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联7种鸟类，如White-throated honeyeater、Gilbert's honeyeater、White-naped honeyeater等7种鸟类。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 7, "x": 535.72, "y": -268.62, "z": 93.12}], "links": [{"key": "bird-strong-billed-honeyeater-c69ed5c6__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-melithreptus-validirostris", "source": "bird-strong-billed-honeyeater-c69ed5c6", "target": "taxonomy-species-melithreptus-validirostris", "relation": "belongs_to_species", "label": "属于种", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 中的种字段补充。"}, {"key": "taxonomy-species-melithreptus-validirostris__belongs_to_genus__taxonomy-genus-melithreptus", "source": "taxonomy-species-melithreptus-validirostris", "target": "taxonomy-genus-melithreptus", "relation": "belongs_to_genus", "label": "属于属", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 分类字段补充：Strong-billed honeyeater 属于属 Melithreptus。"}]}
